# Node.js Package Configuration (package.json)

This file is the package manifest for the Roboshop Catalogue service.

It contains:

- Project Metadata
- Application Version
- NPM Scripts
- Runtime Dependencies
- Development Dependencies

Node.js and NPM use this file to install packages, execute scripts, and manage application versions.

---

# Complete package.json

```json
{
  "name": "catalogue",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "description": "product catalogue REST API",
  "main": "server.js",

  "scripts": {

    "test": "jest --coverage --forceExit",

    "coverage": "jest --coverage --coverageReporters=lcov --forceExit"
  },

  "author": "SteveW",

  "license": "Apache-2.0",

  "dependencies": {

    "body-parser": "^1.18.1",

    "express": "^4.15.4",

    "mongodb": "^4.7.0",

    "pino": "^5.10.8",

    "express-pino-logger": "^4.0.0",

    "pino-pretty": "^2.5.0",

    "@instana/collector": "^1.132.2",

    "redis": "^3.1.1",

    "request": "^2.88.2",

    "prom-client": "^11.5.3"
  },

  "devDependencies": {

    "jest": "^29.0.0",

    "supertest": "^6.3.0"
  }
}
```

---

# What is package.json?

`package.json` is the central configuration file of a Node.js application.

Purpose:

```text
Project Metadata
Dependency Management
Version Control
Build Configuration
Test Execution
```

Without this file:

```bash
npm install
npm test
npm run
```

cannot work correctly.

---

# Architecture Overview

```text
package.json
      │
      ▼
npm install
      │
      ▼
Dependencies
      │
      ▼
Node.js Application
```

---

# Application Name

```json
"name": "catalogue"
```

Defines the application name.

Application:

```text
Catalogue Service
```

Responsible for:

```text
Product Listings
Category Retrieval
Product Search
Product Information
```

within the Roboshop platform.

---

# Application Version

```json
"version": "1.1.0"
```

Uses Semantic Versioning.

Format:

```text
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
```

Current Version:

```text
1.1.0
```

Meaning:

```text
Major Version : 1
Minor Version : 1
Patch Version : 0
```

---

# Description

```json
"description": "product catalogue REST API"
```

Provides a short explanation of the application.

Purpose:

```text
Documentation
Package Metadata
Repository Browsing
```

---

# Main Entry Point

```json
"main": "server.js"
```

Defines the application startup file.

Execution Flow:

```text
Node.js
   │
   ▼
server.js
   │
   ▼
Express Application
```

---

# Scripts Section

```json
"scripts"
```

Contains executable NPM commands.

Usage:

```bash
npm run <script-name>
```

---

# Test Script

```json
"test": "jest --coverage --forceExit"
```

Runs automated tests.

Command:

```bash
npm test
```

Equivalent:

```bash
jest --coverage --forceExit
```

---

# What Happens?

```text
Run Tests
      │
      ▼
Measure Coverage
      │
      ▼
Generate Reports
```

---

# forceExit

```text
--forceExit
```

Forces Jest to terminate after tests complete.

Useful when:

```text
Database Connections Remain Open
Timers Continue Running
Background Processes Exist
```

---

# Coverage Script

```json
"coverage": "jest --coverage --coverageReporters=lcov --forceExit"
```

Generates coverage reports.

Command:

```bash
npm run coverage
```

Produces:

```text
coverage/lcov.info
```

---

# Why LCOV?

LCOV is commonly consumed by:

- :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

for coverage analysis.

